19":"1219","Trefrant, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom":"Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ab","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Turkish: ornamental name or nickname from <i>ay</i> ‘Moon’, by extension also ‘beautiful face’.","Hungarian (<b>Áy</b>): unexplained.","Chinese: alternative Mandarin form of the surname 艾, see   Ai   2."],"variants":[{"name":"Ai","meanings":["Japanese: usually written 阿井 with characters used phonetically. The meaning could be ‘meeting’. In North America, it may also be a shortened form of some other name.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 艾, referring to ‘Chinese mugwort’, a type of plant used in traditional Chinese medical treatment: (i) perhaps from the second element of Ru Ai (汝艾), the name of an official who lived during the reign of Shao Kang, the 6th king of the Xia dynasty (2070–1600  BC ). (ii) from the first element of the placename Ai Ling (艾陵), the name of a hill (located in Shandong province), the fief of Ai Kong (艾孔), an official in the state of Qi during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iii) from the placename Ai (艾), the name of a fief (located in Jiangxi province) which was granted to an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iv) adopted as a surname by the Qu Jin (去斤), Qu Ai (去艾), and Ai Jin (艾斤) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (v) from Ai (艾), the name of an ancient state (possibly in present-day Jiangxi province) during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 愛, meaning ‘love’ in Chinese: (i) said to be traced back to Ai Xie Wu (愛邪勿), prime minister of the state of Huihu (known as Uyghur Empire or Uyghur Khaganate), who was endowed with the surname Ai (愛) by Emperor Wuzong of Tang (814–846  AD ). (ii) a Han Chinese surname for some members of the Aisin Gioro family from the Manchu ethnic group, known as the royal family of the Qing dynasty (1616 – 1911  AD ). (iii) a surname from minority ethnic groups in Taiwan."]}]},{"name":"Ithel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name derived from the Greek, signifying 'blooming luxuriantly, flourishing, rich.'. It is from Ithel that we have first the name Ap-Ithel, then by corruption, Bithell and Bethell."],"variants":[{"name":"Bithell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]},{"name":"Bethell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]}]},{"name":"Llwyd","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Same as Lhuyd, q v."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Rhiwallon Llwyd ab Ithel was born about 1209, in Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Rhiwallon Llwyd ab Ithel."},"et":{"about 1209–":"umbes 1209–Surnud","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1219–Male":"1219–Surnud","1209–Female":"1209–Surnud","1205":"1205","about 1219":"umbes 1219","about 1209":"umbes 1209","1209":"1209","1219":"1219","Trefrant, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom":"Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1209–":"noin 1209–Kuollut","1205–Male":"1205–Kuollut","1219–Male":"1219–Kuollut","1209–Female":"1209–Kuollut","1205":"1205","about 1219":"noin 1219","about 1209":"noin 1209","1209":"1209","1219":"1219","Trefrant, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom":"Gwent, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1209–":"environ 1209–Décédée","1205–Male":"1205–Décédé","1219–Male":"1219–Décédé","1209–Female":"1209–Décédée","1205":"1205","about 1219":"environ 1219","about 1209":"environ 1209","1209":"1209","1219":"1219","Trefrant, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Gwent, Wales, United Kingdom":"Gwent, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Rhiwallon Llwyd ab Ithel est née environ 1209, à Gwent, Pays de Galles